text: Sweets really is the case of: you want it when you can't have (much of) it. When I was a student I bought sweets all the time to keep up... And after I graduated I didn't buy sweets for like two years. It just lost its appeal. And I still  many years later  don't like things that are just sweet; I only want things that have a strong flavor of something else like coco or lemon. And yeh I know sugar addiction is real  but I guess for me the association between sugar and studying was so strong and off-putting that I just didn't fall for the addiction.
